<hr>
<strong>WORKS CITED</strong>
<br><br>
Add a &#8216;Works Cited&#8217; entry at the end of your essay citing all sources used in the body of your writing.
<br><br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	Editor&#8217;s Name, editor. <em>Title of Book</em>. Publisher, year of	publication.
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Examples</strong>
<br>
If the publisher is an academic press, replace <em>Press</em> with <em>P</em>. For further information on publisher abbreviations, see 1.6.3 in the <a href="http://west-sydney-primo.hosted.exlibrisgroup.com/UWS-ALMA:default_scope:UWS-ALMA21186157620001571" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">MLA Handbook (8th edition)</a>.
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	<span class="hover" title="Editor&#8217;s Name">Smith, Amy, editor.</span>
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of Book">Invertebrate Taxonomy</span></em>.
	<span class="hover" title="Publisher">Kowhai P</span>, 
	<span class="hover" title="year of publication">2056</span>.
</blockquote>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	<span class="hover" title="Editor&#8217;s Name">Smith, Amy, and Bridget Brown, editors.</span> 
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of Book">Sustainability in Practice: Overcoming Energy Challenges in the 21st Century</span></em>.
	<span class="hover" title="Publisher">Northwoods</span>, 
	<span class="hover" title="year of publication">2056</span>.
</blockquote>
<br>
	If the source has three or more editors, provide the name of the first editor followed by et al. in the Works Cited entry and in-text. See ‘Book, three or more authors’ for examples. 
